post_cb({"8586203": {"LastActivityDate": "2011-12-21T07:40:21.827", "CommentCount": "6", "Body": "<p>From your edit: 12.2 states that a temporary is created in the cases when you initialize a const reference where it refers to a prvalue. For example:</p>\n<pre><code>double d = 3.14;\nconst int &amp;r = d;\n</code></pre>\n<p>the compiler transforms this code into something like this:</p>\n<pre><code>  int temp = d;         // creates a temporary int\n  const int &amp;r = temp;  // reference is bound to that temporary\n</code></pre>\n<p>The lifetime of temporary that is bound to a const reference is the lifetime of the reference. i.e. the temporary is destroyed when the reference goes out of the scope.</p>\n", "CreationDate": "2011-12-21T07:10:55.757", "LastEditDate": "2011-12-21T07:40:21.827", "ParentId": "8586108", "Id": "8586203", "LastEditorUserId": "187543", "PostTypeId": "2", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "187543"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_8586108_8586108_0": {"length": 18, "quality": 0.6, "section_id": 378}}, "n3337": {"so_8586108_8586108_0": {"length": 19, "quality": 0.6333333333333333, "section_id": 369}}}, "8586108": {"CreationDate": "2011-12-21T06:55:24.523", "ViewCount": "271", "FavoriteCount": "0", "Id": "8586108", "AcceptedAnswerId": "8586203", "Score": "2", "Title": "How do temporary objects get created during Reference initialization?", "LastEditorUserId": "462608", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>How do temporary objects get created during reference initialization by the compiler, and what does that mean?</p>\n<h2>EDIT</h2>\n<p>From the C++ standard:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_8586108_8586108_0\">12.2    Temporary objects                                                                [class.temporary]   Temporaries of class type are created in various\n  contexts: <strong><em>binding a reference to a prvalue</em></strong> (8.5.3), returning 1   a\n  prvalue (6.6.3), a conversion that creates a prvalue (4.1, 5.2.9,\n  5.2.11, 5.4), throwing an exception (15.1),   entering a handler (15.3), and in some initializations (8.5).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>From this link: <a href=\"http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/lnxpcomp/v8v101/index.jsp?topic=%2Fcom.ibm.xlcpp8l.doc%2Flanguage%2Fref%2Fcplr382.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/lnxpcomp/v8v101/index.jsp?topic=%2Fcom.ibm.xlcpp8l.doc%2Flanguage%2Fref%2Fcplr382.htm</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_8586108_8586108_1\">When a temporary object is created to initialize a reference variable,\n  the name of the temporary object has the same scope as that of the\n  reference variable.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "Tags": "<c++><reference>", "LastEditDate": "2011-12-21T07:20:15.577", "LastActivityDate": "2011-12-21T07:40:21.827", "PostTypeId": "1", "AnswerCount": "1", "OwnerUserId": "462608"}});